      • createBranch

        private static DewInterpreter.DewParser.SyntaxBranch createBranch(DewInterpreter.DewLexer.LexicalTokens.LexicalToken branchTriggerToken,
                                                 int branchTriggerTokenIndex,
                                                 java.util.ArrayList<DewInterpreter.DewLexer.LexicalTokens.LexicalToken> lexicalTokens,
                                                 java.util.ArrayList<DewInterpreter.DewParser.ParseTokens.Variable> globalVariableList,
                                                 java.util.ArrayList<DewInterpreter.DewParser.ParseTokens.Variable> localVariableList,
                                                 java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Short> globalVariablePointersMap,
                                                 java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Short> localVariablePointersMap,
                                                 short depth,
                                                 org.apache.commons.lang3.mutable.MutableInt branchLoopIndex)
                                                           throws DewInterpreter.DewException
        This recursive method creates a syntax tree by processing a Stack containing tokenized DewScript scource. It handles expression evaluation and subbranching as necessary. It handles variable scope as necessary. It handles variable pointers as necessary.
        Parameters:
        branchTriggerToken - the token that flagged the method to make a recursive call and evaulate a subbranch.
        branchTriggerTokenIndex - the index of the arrayList that flagged the method to make a recursive call and evaulate a subbranch.
        lexicalTokens - an ArrayList containing the lexical tokens from the lexer to be parsed and assembled into a syntax tree or subbranch.
        globalVariableList - the ArrayList containg the highest level branch's (the trunk, or starting branch of the tree) variables. Any variabel declared as public should added to this list to ensure public scope.
        localVariableList - the ArrayList conaining private variables only relative to the current subbranch. Variables added to this list are not passed up the syntax tree as this list is cloned in subbraches to keep the security of variabel scope. Varibles added to this list will be passed to subbranches.
        globalVariablePointersMap - the HashMap containig the highest level branch's (the trunk, or starting branch of the tree) variable pointers. Any varible delcared as public should have it's pointer added to this Map to ensure global scope.
        localVariablePointersMap - the HashMap containg pointers to variables relative to the current subbranch. Pointers added to this Map are not passed up the syntax tree as this list is cloned in subbranches to keep the security of variable scope. Pointers added to this list will be passed to subbranches.
        depth - the depth of the subbranch, currently used for debugging purposes. Likely to be removed.
        branchLoopIndex - the MutableInt represinting the looping index of the super branch. As tokens are used by the subbranch, the super branch no longer needs to evalutate them becuase they only belong to the subbranch. Evaluating them else where would cause the syntax tree to redundant and wrong evlauations. A MutableInt is used to keep a pointer to the looping index of the superbranch,incrementing it as the subbranch evlauated tokens. This ensures when the subbranch has been evaluated, the superbranch will where to pick up the evaluation process in teh ArrayList.
        Returns:
        the syntax branch to be added to the syntax tree for evaluation.
        Throws:
        DewInterpreter.DewException - if the syntax rules of DewScript are violated or if the parser experiences an internal error, a DewException will be thrown.
